How to build primesieve:

  1. Microsoft Visual C++
    Open a Visual Studio Command Prompt, cd into the primesieve
    directory and run:
    > nmake -f Makefile.msvc
  
  2. G++ GNU Compiler 
    Open a terminal, cd into the primesieve directory and run:
    $ make
    
  3. Other C++ compilers
    Open a terminal, cd into the primesieve directory and run:
    $ make CXX=my_compiler

How to test primesieve:

  1. Windows
    > out\primesieve.exe 1 1000 -p1
    Prints the prime numbers up to 1000 to the standard output.
    
  2. Unix-like operating systems (Linux, Mac OS X, FreeBSD, ...)
    $ out/./primesieve 1 10000000000 -c1 -c2 -s 32
    Counts the prime numbers and twin primes up to 10^10 using a
    sieve size of 32 KiloBytes.
    The results should be 455052511 prime numbers and 27412679 
    twin primes.
